<section id="Tagging_a_Resource_Pool" remap="TID_15345">
	<title>Tagging a Resource Pool</title>
	<para>
		Use tags to categorize a resource pool. Before assigning tags, create them using the instructions in the <emphasis>CloudForms Management Engine Settings and Operations Guide</emphasis>.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Tag a Resource Pool</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>Resource Pools</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the resource pool to tag.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1941.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Policy)</guibutton>, and then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2158.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Edit Tags)</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Select a customer tag from the first dropdown, and then a value for the tag.
			</para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/2233.png" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>